# Next.js + TypeScript Guardrails

- Prefer App Router conventions and server-first data access where practical.
- Keep route handlers thin; move reusable logic into `lib/` modules.
- Use explicit types on public function boundaries and exported objects.
- Avoid `any`; if unavoidable, narrow quickly and document why.
- Never leak secrets to client bundles; only expose `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars intentionally.
- Add or update tests for behavioral changes in core flows.
